Responses.NAM1 - Response Text: What can I do for you, outlander?
I have no more business for you.
Why not speak with Crassius Curio or Edryno Arethi?
They both live in the Hlaalu Canton in Vivec.
Curio Manor is in the Plaza, and Edryno lives in the Waistworks.
Business as usual, except for the ebony trade.
Ralen Hlaalu was murdered recently.
I would ask for you to retaliate against this crime, but perhaps you've found Ralen Hlaalo's murderer already...
A Hlaalu noble was recently murdered. I need someone to find out who killed Ralen Hlaalo.
No. I heard you killed Bivale Teneran.
I will not discuss business with you any more.
I need someone to deliver new orders to Bivale Teneran.
House Redoran sells more guar hides than House Hlaalu.
Someone needs to convince the alchemists in Vivec to buy only imported House Hlaalu guar hides.
A rival of House Hlaalu gets his wealth from an egg mine.
I need someone to destroy this rival's wealth by killing the queen in the Inanius egg mine.
I need someone to visit an apothecary in Vivec and... acquire certain alchemical formulas.
Like I said, wear Felsen Sethandus' helm and use the phrase "orphan of Arnesia" with Neminda in Ald'ruhn.
Like I said, wear Relmerea Saram's helm and use the phrase "orphan of Arnesia" with Neminda in Ald'ruhn.
I need someone to deliver new orders to Bivale Teneran.
If you want to talk business, you've come to the right place. Do you want to join House Hlaalu?
You are not a member of House Hlaalu, outlander. Business here is only conducted with House Hlaalu members.
I need someone to collect a debt from Murudius Flaeus.
Bandits are always bad for business. Because of bandits on the road to Pelagiad, the Hlaalu trader Tarvyn Faren needs an escort.
Not business today, but duty. House Hlaalu sent a team to an illegal Telvanni base, but they have not returned from Odirniran.
Today's business involves Yngling Half-Troll's prized game rats.
The business of Vvardenfell is the ebony trade.
A ship wrecked off Azura's coast over a year ago. I need someone to find the wreckage of the Prelude.
Thieves have broken into a shop here in Vivec three nights in a row. I need someone to defend Ralen Tilvur's shop.
It's business as usual in Vivec. Speak with Crassius Curio at his manor here in the Hlaalu Compound or speak with Nileno Dorvayn in Balmora.
You're doing well, Dumpling. Just speak with Odral Helvi again and keep me informed.
Make sure Odral Helvi gets arrested for the shipment of ebony he wants my little sweetheart to deliver.
Now that you've had some experience in ebony smuggling, pudding pie, I want you to look for Velfred the Outlaw.
You know how I feel about you, but I just can't discuss business with you right now.
Have you checked your advancement in House Hlaalu, Dumpling?
You also need to build yourself a stronghold.
You know how I feel about you, but I just can't discuss business with you right now.
Have you checked your advancement in House Hlaalu, Dumpling?
House Redoran built a stronghold without a charter from the Duke.
You're the perfect one to teach Redoran Lord Banden Indarys a lesson.
It would be a good idea to win the support of another Councilman, my sweet.
Of all the Councilmen, I believe only Dram Bero has the courage to support an outlander.
You know how I feel about you, but I just can't discuss business with anyone under the rank of House Father.
The naughty Telvanni also built a stronghold without a charter.
Before the Duke grants this stronghold legitimacy, I want you to deal with the Telvanni sorcerer Reynel Uvirith.
I have no more business for you, Dumpling.
Maybe it's time you were introduced to Duke Vedam Dren in Ebonheart.
I need a courier to deliver a package of sealed orders.
Important documents are missing from the offices here in Caldera.
I need someone to catch whoever stole the Caldera mining contracts.
There is an error in some of the documents in the Hall of Records.
I need someone to replace these erroneous documents.
I am responsible for land in the Ascadian Isles and at this time of year, I need to collect the rent and taxes from the farmers.
I need you deliver a shipment of ebony to a friend of mine.
There is no business that must be done here in Caldera.
You know how I feel about you, but I just can't discuss business with you until you have improved the business around your Stronghold.
Business? How can you talk about business when people cannot read?
The real business of Vvardenfell is slavery.
You have done all that I would ask. Speak with Crassius Curio or my father, Duke Dren.
In order for House Hlaalu and the most virtuous aspects of the Empire to survive, we must find a way to control the Ordinators.
To be Grandaster in anything other than name, you must win control of the Camonna Tong from my brother, Orvas Dren.
I see. You wish to learn of Ashlanders from me. And what is it that you wish to learn?
Yes, my friend. You say you want to ask me some questions. What would you wish to know about the Ashlanders and the Nerevarine cult?
Or perhaps you wish to know more about my life as a trader?
Let's try again, shall we? I propose to give you an artifact called 'Wraithguard."
You may accept the gift, then do with it as you will.
I propose that you accept the responsibility of defeating Dagoth Ur, and swearing an oath to that effect.
You may give your oath, then keep it or break it as you like.
First, will you accept Wraithguard as a gift?
When I was young like you, I was very impatient. So I will keep our business short. Then, later, there may be time for other things.
First, I propose to remove my curse upon the Nerevarine, end the persecution of the Dissident Priests.
I will proclaim to all Morrowind that You are the Incarnate and Nerevarine, the prophesied savior of Morrowind...
and the last hope to withstand the menace of Dagoth Ur and the Sixth House.
These things I will do, whether you wish or not.
Next, I propose to surrender to you the power and responsibility of defeating Dagoth Ur.
You may choose to refuse; I will not compel you.
You will receive the power as a gift, in the form of an artifact called 'Wraithguard."
You may accept the gift, then do with it as you will.
You will receive the responsibility as an oath. You may give your oath, then keep it or break it as you like.
First, will you accept Wraithguard as a gift?
Let's see. You accepted an artifact called Wraithguard.
Then I proposed that you accept the responsibility of defeating Dagoth Ur, and swearing an oath to that effect.
You may give your oath, then keep it or break it as you like.
So. Will you give your oath?
...before all gods and men, before all spirits visible and invisible, before my honor and your honor...
...to dedicate yourself and Wraithguard to the defeat and destruction of Dagoth Ur.
And to the preservation of Morrowind and its people?
Actually, I believe we've finished our business.
I will notify the Temple that you are our champion.
There shall be no more persecution of the Dissident Priests, and I hope both sides shall swiftly be reconciled.
Now you are my guest, I am your host, and we have time for explanations....
Or counsel...
Or questions...
Or bitter recriminations, if you like.
Or you may leave, if you wish.  As you wish.
But I think before you leave you should hear how to defeat Dagoth Ur, and how you must use the artifact Wraithguard.
Surely you do not expect me to discuss business with you when you have broken the rules. You must make amends, outlander.
House Hlaalu's business is in your hands now, outlander.
Perhaps I will discuss business with you when you have earned a higher rank in House Hlaalu.
How can I trust you if you cannot stick to the simple rules of House Hlaalu?
What business? Prove yourself in House Hlaalu and then perhaps we can discuss business.
You've broken the rules of House Hlaalu, sweetie. It brings tears to my eyes when I think about your disloyalty.
Maybe you can make amends and make everything better.
I can't talk about business to anyone who doesn't belong to House Hlaalu, sweetie.
Speak with Odral Helvi in Caldera. Turn your charms on him, sweetie, and talk about business.
If you feel his request is questionable, speak with me for further directions. Keep Uncle Crassius well informed, and I'll reward you.
I do not have any business for you right now, Dumpling.
I don't think so. You've been expelled.
You've been expelled. Go up to the Plaza and talk with Crassius Curio to make amends.
Yes, of course, I need a courier to deliver this sealed report.
You've been expelled. I can't give you duties, but perhaps I can help you make amends.
I need someone to visit an apothecary in Vivec and... acquire certain alchemical formulas.
I need someone to visit an apothecary in Vivec and... acquire certain alchemical formulas.
Just a minute, outlander. Say that again.
If you want to talk business, you've come to the right place. Do you want to join House Hlaalu?
If you want to talk business, speak with Nileno Dorvayn.
If you want to talk business, speak with Crassius Curio or Edryno Arethi.
Hmm.  At a second glance, perhaps I shouldn't be so dismissive.  You seem a rather resourceful sort.  We're, ah, investing in the future, you see.
The city right now exists under a blanket of fear;
a blind guar can see that the tension between the Imperials and the Temple will soon be boiling over into the streets.
When that happens, it's going to be everyone for himself, yes?
Well, we're stockpiling for just that occasion, which is certainly inevitable at this point.  And maybe you can assist us.
I don't recall inviting you to discuss the issue; you can't be trusted.  Keep walking, outlander.
It's no concern of yours, outlander.
You've done more than enough for us, outlander. Thank you for your help.
Yes, let's discuss what you can do to assist my, err, our cause.
